### Failure Mode 4: Static Member Fencing Grace Period Boundary Condition

**Risk**: MEDIUM

**Code Location**: GroupMetadataManager.java ~lines 1627-1635 (throwIfInstanceIdIsUnreleased), ~lines 4059-4089 (consumerGroupLeave for static members), ~lines 4137-4153 (consumerGroupStaticMemberGroupLeave)

**Description**:
The coordinator implements a grace period for static members marked with `LEAVE_GROUP_STATIC_MEMBER_EPOCH (-2)`. When a static member with instance ID is marked with epoch -2, the coordinator allows the same instance ID to be reassigned only after a grace period (session timeout).

The test suite has tests for this behavior, but lacks coverage for exact boundary conditions:
1. Static member A with instance ID "inst-1" leaves with epoch -2 at time T
2. New member B tries to join with same instance ID "inst-1" at time T + (session_timeout - 1ms)
3. The coordinator should reject with `UNRELEASED_INSTANCE_ID`
4. At time T + (session_timeout + 1ms), member B should be allowed to join

The edge case is in the timing logic around when the grace period expires. The current code at line 1628 checks if `memberEpoch() != LEAVE_GROUP_STATIC_MEMBER_EPOCH`, but this doesn't account for the timeout grace period expiration.

**Proposed Test**:
```java
@Test
public void testStaticMemberFencingGracePeriodBoundary() {
    String groupId = "test-group";
    String instanceId = "instance-1";
    String member1Id = Uuid.randomUuid().toString();
    String member2Id = Uuid.randomUuid().toString();

    MockPartitionAssignor assignor = new MockPartitionAssignor("range");
    GroupMetadataManagerTestContext context = new GroupMetadataManagerTestContext.Builder()
        .withConfig(GroupCoordinatorConfig.CONSUMER_GROUP_ASSIGNORS_CONFIG, List.of(assignor))
        .build();

    // Member 1 joins with static instance ID
    CoordinatorResult<ConsumerGroupHeartbeatResponseData, CoordinatorRecord> result =
        context.consumerGroupHeartbeat(new ConsumerGroupHeartbeatRequestData()
            .setGroupId(groupId)
            .setMemberId(member1Id)
            .setMemberEpoch(0)
            .setInstanceId(instanceId)
            .setRebalanceTimeoutMs(60000)
            .setSubscribedTopicNames(List.of("test-topic"))
            .setTopicPartitions(List.of()));

    long currentTime = context.time().milliseconds();

    // Member 1 leaves with static member epoch -2
    result = context.consumerGroupHeartbeat(new ConsumerGroupHeartbeatRequestData()
        .setGroupId(groupId)
        .setMemberId(member1Id)
        .setMemberEpoch(LEAVE_GROUP_STATIC_MEMBER_EPOCH)
        .setInstanceId(instanceId));

    // Immediately try to join with different member ID and same instance ID
    // Should be rejected because grace period hasn't expired
    assertThrows(UnreleasedInstanceIdException.class, () ->
        context.consumerGroupHeartbeat(new ConsumerGroupHeartbeatRequestData()
            .setGroupId(groupId)
            .setMemberId(member2Id)
            .setMemberEpoch(0)
            .setInstanceId(instanceId)
            .setRebalanceTimeoutMs(60000)
            .setSubscribedTopicNames(List.of("test-topic"))
            .setTopicPartitions(List.of()))
    );

    // Advance time to just before grace period expires
    int sessionTimeoutMs = 45000; // Default consumer group session timeout
    context.sleep(sessionTimeoutMs - 1);

    // Still should be rejected (1ms before grace period)
    assertThrows(UnreleasedInstanceIdException.class, () ->
        context.consumerGroupHeartbeat(new ConsumerGroupHeartbeatRequestData()
            .setGroupId(groupId)
            .setMemberId(member2Id)
            .setMemberEpoch(0)
            .setInstanceId(instanceId)
            .setRebalanceTimeoutMs(60000)
            .setSubscribedTopicNames(List.of("test-topic"))
            .setTopicPartitions(List.of()))
    );

    // Advance time past grace period
    context.sleep(2); // Total: sessionTimeoutMs + 1

    // Now should be allowed to join with different member ID
    result = context.consumerGroupHeartbeat(new ConsumerGroupHeartbeatRequestData()
        .setGroupId(groupId)
        .setMemberId(member2Id)
        .setMemberEpoch(0)
        .setInstanceId(instanceId)
        .setRebalanceTimeoutMs(60000)
        .setSubscribedTopicNames(List.of("test-topic"))
        .setTopicPartitions(List.of()));

    assertEquals(1, result.response().memberEpoch());
    assertEquals(member2Id, result.response().memberId());
}
```

